  "prompt": "How is Iphone 6s better than 6?",
  "response": "The iPhone 6s introduced several improvements over the iPhone 6, enhancing both performance and functionality. Here are some key differences that highlight how the iPhone 6s is better than the iPhone 6:\n\n1. **3D Touch**: The iPhone 6s features 3D Touch technology, which allows the screen to detect different levels of pressure, enabling new gestures and shortcuts.\n\n2. **Improved Camera**: The iPhone 6s has a 12 MP rear camera, compared to the 8 MP camera in the iPhone 6. This results in sharper images and better overall photo quality. The 6s also supports 4K video recording, whereas the iPhone 6 does not.\n\n3. **Front Camera and Live Photos**: The front camera on the iPhone 6s is a 5 MP shooter, up from 1.2 MP in the iPhone 6, which allows for better selfies and video calls. The iPhone 6s also introduced Live Photos, which captures a few seconds of video along with still photos.\n\n4. **Faster Processor**: The iPhone 6s is powered by the A9 chip, which provides improved performance and efficiency compared to the A8 chip in the iPhone 6. This results in faster app launches, better gaming performance, and improved battery management.\n\n5. **More RAM**: The iPhone 6s has 2 GB of RAM, while the iPhone 6 has only 1 GB. This allows for better multitasking capabilities and overall smoother performance.\n\n6. **Build Quality**: The iPhone 6s features a stronger 7000 series aluminum body, making it more durable than the iPhone 6, which has a softer aluminum.\n\n7. **Color Options**: The iPhone 6s introduced the Rose Gold color option, along with the standard Silver, Gold, and Space Gray options.\n\nOverall, the enhancements in performance, camera capabilities, and new features like 3D Touch and Live Photos make the iPhone 6s a significant improvement over the iPhone 6.",
